title: Natalia Pakulska
text:
Natalia Pakulska (born 27 November 1991) is a Polish <a href="women%27s%20soccer">football</a> <a href="midfielder">midfielder</a>, currently playing for <a href="KKPK%20Medyk%20Konin">Medyk Konin</a> in Poland's <a href="Ekstraliga%20Kobiet">Ekstraliga</a>.
She is a member of the <a href="Poland%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Polish national team</a>.
Personal life.
Pakulska was born in <a href="Brze%C5%9B%C4%87%20Kujawski">Brześć Kujawski</a>. She studies <a href="physical%20education">physical education</a> in the <a href="Pa%C5%84stwowa%20Wy%C5%BCsza%20Szko%C5%82a%20Zawodowa">Państwowa Wyższa Szkoła Zawodowa</a>.
Club career.
She started playing against local boys in her home town of <a href="Brze%C5%9B%C4%87%20Kujawski">Brześć Kujawski</a> at the age of 9. After joining "Duet Włocławek", she was spotted by <a href="Scout%20%28sport%29">scouts</a> when the team took part in a women's tournament in <a href="Konin">Konin</a> and was invited to train at <a href="KKPK%20Medyk%20Konin">Medyk Konin</a>, who she joined at the age of 14 under the <a href="Coach%20%28sport%29">coaching</a> of <a href="Anna%20Gawro%C5%84ska">Anna Gawrońska</a>.
